---
alwaysApply: false
---
> 此規則檔為團隊共同遵循，歡迎提出優化建議！
description: >
  These are cursor rules for Python files to aid navigation, understanding, and editing.
matches:
  - name: Function Definition
    matcher:
      type: regex
      pattern: '^\s*def\s+\w+\(.*\):'
    actions:
      - move: toStart
        description: Move cursor to the start of the function definition.
      - select: block
        description: Select the entire function block.

  - name: Class Definition
    matcher:
      type: regex
      pattern: '^\s*class\s+\w+\(?.*\)?:'
    actions:
      - move: toStart
        description: Move cursor to the start of the class definition.
      - select: block
        description: Select the entire class block.

  - name: Comment Line
    matcher:
      type: regex
      pattern: '^\s*#.*'
    actions:
      - select: line
        description: Select the comment line.

  - name: Import Statement
    matcher:
      type: regex
      pattern: '^\s*(import|from)\s+\w+'
    actions:
      - select: line
        description: 選取 import 陳述式這一行。
  - name: String Literal
    matcher:
      type: regex
      pattern: '"([^"\\]|\\.)*"|\'([^\'\\]|\\.)*\''
    actions:
      - select: token
        description: Select the quoted string.

  - name: Docstring
    matcher:
      type: regex
      pattern: '^\s*[ruRU]{0,2}"""(?:.|\n)*?"""|^\s*[ruRU]{0,2}\'\'\'(?:.|\n)*?\'\'\''
    actions:
      - select: block
        description: Select the whole docstring.


